        <h4>Wiki terms and conditions</h4>
        
        <p>The following are the terms and conditions of use of the site. </p>
        <br />
        <p>You must be a current student of a club linked to the Midlands Wing Chun Society and be a practicing student. 
        You are encouraged to use the site to aid in your study of the art to expand your understanding of the techniques 
        and our knowledge of the art form. You are encouraged to practice what you see but do so in a safe manner. You may 
        copy and store any images here and add them to your own personal notebooks. You may upload images you have taken 
        during your own training sessions, you may also add information about the images, when you found them useful, what form 
        the techniques displayed are from so that others may increase their understanding of the art and improve the art for themselves.
        You may not under any circumstances upload images that are or have any sexual content, any-one found doing so will 
        immediatley be banned from the site and reported to their instructor and the head instructor of our society. </p>
        
        <p>Please remember this site has been created to aid students and to make sure that this wonderful art form can
        evolve without the loss of knowledge. Please remember the principals of Wing Chun and help to foster them through 
        the society and through this site, to keep an open and inclusive spirit of friendship and co-operation so that we may all 
        grow together. </p>
        
